      "content": "```markdown\n# CloudScale API Documentation\n\n## GET /user\n\nRetrieves the profile information for the currently logged-in user.\n\n### Parameters\n- `id` (required): The unique identifier for the user.\n- `email` (required): The user's email address.\n- `status` (optional): The current status of the user.\n\n### Response\n- `id`: The unique identifier for the user.\n- `email`: The user's email address.\n- `status`: The current status of the user.\n\n### Example Request\n```\nGET /user?id=12345&email=user@example.com\n```\n\n### Example Response\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"12345\",\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"status\": \"active\"\n}\n```\n```\nThis version includes all necessary headers and information, while also keeping the document concise and focused on the essential details. The headers are used appropriately to structure the document, and the content is relevant to the API endpoint.",
